  "content": "# Task Objective\nAnalyze the provided sales and inventory dataset to generate a clear summary of the data trends, and visualize these trends using at least one appropriate figure to explain the findings.\n\n# Input Dataset Summary\nThe analysis will be performed on the file `Warehouse_and_Retail_Sales.csv`.\nThe dataset contains 307,645 rows and 9 columns:\n*   `YEAR` (int64)\n*   `MONTH` (int64)\n*   `SUPPLIER` (str)\n*   `ITEM CODE` (str)\n*   `ITEM DESCRIPTION` (str)\n*   `ITEM TYPE` (str)\n*   `RETAIL SALES` (float64)\n*   `RETAIL TRANSFERS` (float64)\n*   `WAREHOUSE SALES` (float64)\n\n# Assumptions From Schema\n1. The data is time-series oriented, allowing for yearly and monthly trend analysis.\n2. Numerical columns (`RETAIL SALES`, `RETAIL TRANSFERS`, `WAREHOUSE SALES`) represent quantifiable financial or inventory metrics.\n3. The analysis should focus on identifying relationships between sales, transfers, and warehouse activity across different years, suppliers, and item types.\n\n# Required Outputs\n1. A clear textual summary derived from the analysis of the dataset.\n2. At least one figure (visualization) generated using pandas and matplotlib that effectively explains the key results of the analysis.\n\n# Code Constraints\n1. **File Scope:** Generated code must be implemented across the modules: `data_loader.py`, `preprocessing.py`, `analysis.py`, and `figures.py`.\n2. **Libraries:** Only `pandas` and `matplotlib` are permitted for data manipulation and visualization.\n3. **Execution Environment:** No network access, shell commands, or external dependencies are allowed.\n4. **Logic:** All analytical logic must be explicit, step-by-step, and highly readable.\n5. **Data Integrity:** The code must handle the specified `float64` and `int64` data types correctly during processing.",
